            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1434851935,
            "creation_date": 1434851935,
            "body": "<blockquote>\n  <p>But I'm not expecting most end users to have PATH setup and all that, so I'm concerned that these solutions could run into problems there. <\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>Using the <code>javax.tools<\/code> approach (described in the Q&amp;A you linked to) does not require the user to set <code>$PATH<\/code> or <code>$JAVA_HOME<\/code> or <code>$CLASS_PATH<\/code>.  AFAIK, all it requires is that the user is running <code>java<\/code> from a JDK install.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 30960578,
            "question_id": 30960204
        },
